36/**
37 * \file
38 *
39 * This file contains functions to help a module keep track of the
40 * queries it has outstanding to authoritative servers.
41 */
42#include "config.h"
43#include <sys/time.h>
44#include "services/outbound_list.h"
45#include "services/outside_network.h"
46
47void
48outbound_list_init(struct outbound_list* list)
49{
50 list->first = NULL;
51}
52
53void
54outbound_list_clear(struct outbound_list* list)
55{
56 struct outbound_entry *p, *np;
57 p = list->first;
58 while(p) {
59 np = p->next;
60 outnet_serviced_query_stop(p->qsent, p);
61 /* in region, no free needed */
62 p = np;
63 }
64 outbound_list_init(list);
65}
66
67void
68outbound_list_insert(struct outbound_list* list, struct outbound_entry* e)
69{
70 if(list->first)
71 list->first->prev = e;
72 e->next = list->first;
73 e->prev = NULL;
74 list->first = e;
75}
76
77void
78outbound_list_remove(struct outbound_list* list, struct outbound_entry* e)
79{
80 if(!e)
81 return;
82 outnet_serviced_query_stop(e->qsent, e);
83 if(e->next)
84 e->next->prev = e->prev;
85 if(e->prev)
86 e->prev->next = e->next;
87 else list->first = e->next;
88 /* in region, no free needed */
89}
